target_assessment.type_match_reasoning: The auditor failed to identify any vulnerabilities, including the target arithmetic error.

notes: The auditor completely missed the critical logic error in the addLiquidity function. The contract uses an average of ratios (baseRatio + tokenRatio) / 2 instead of the minimum (min(baseRatio, tokenRatio)). This is a well-known vulnerability from the Spartan Protocol incident, where an attacker can provide a tiny amount of one asset and a large amount of another to mint an inflated number of LP units, subsequently draining the pool.
